shout /ʃaʊt/

(shouting,shouted,shouts) 

1. V-T/V-I If you shout , you say something very loudly, usually because you want people a long distance away to hear you or because you are angry. 大声说出; 大喊 

例： He had to shout to make himself heard above the wind. 他不得不大喊，好让别人能在风中听见。 

例： 'She's alive!' he shouted triumphantly. “她活着！”他狂喜地大喊。 

例： Andrew rushed out of the house, shouting for help. 安德鲁冲出房子大喊救命。 

2. N-COUNT Shout is also a noun. 大喊 

例： The decision was greeted with shouts of protest from the crowd. 这项决定遭到了人群抗议的呼喊。

